          <h2 id="getting-started">Getting Started</h2>
          <h3>Accessing the Website</h3>
          <ul>
              <li>Open your web browser.</li>
              <li>Enter the URL: <a href="http://localhost:3000/">http://localhost:3000/</a></li>
              <li>Press Enter to load the website.</li>
          </ul>
          
          <h2 id="room-management">Room Management</h2>
          <h3>Adding a New Room</h3>
          <ol>
              <li>Go to <a href="http://localhost:3000/browse/">Browse</a> in the sidebar.</li>
              <li>Click on <a href="http://localhost:3000/browse/room/">Rooms</a></li>
              <li>Click on "Add".</li>
              <li>Fill in the room details: Room ID, Status, Room Type, Price Per Night, Max Adult, Max Child, Room State, Service ID.</li>
              <li>Click "Submit" to add the room to your database.</li>
          </ol>
          <h3>Updating Room Details</h3>
          <ol>
              <li>Go to "Update".</li>
              <li>Type Room ID that you want to edit.</li>
              <li>Update the necessary details.</li>
              <li>We can update new service for room by typing new Service ID in update popup. </li>
              <li>Click "Submit" to apply changes.</li>
          </ol>
          <h3>Deleting a Room</h3>
          <ol>
              <li>Go to "Delete”.</li>
              <li>Type Room ID that you want to delete.</li>
              <li>We can also delete a service id of a room by entering the room id of that room and entering the service id we want.</li>
              <li>Click "Delete" and confirm the action.</li>
          </ol>
          <h3>Viewing all Room</h3>
          <ul>
              <li>Scroll down to see all Room Table.</li>
              <li>Click on 3doc icon to see all info of a Room.</li>
              <li>Click on right arrow to see the next page and left arrow to see the previous page.</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>Page function</h3>
          <ul>
              <li>Click on the search bar and type what you want to find it in the table.</li>
              <li>We can choose date for table by click on date seletor.</li>
              <li>Click on the page number to go to that page.</li>
              <li>Click on "Add new file" button to update new data for this table.</li>
              <li>Click on "Export" button to export file.</li>
          </ul>
          
